  # Python Best Practices
  
  [PEP 8 -- Style Guide for Python Code \\| Python.org](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0008/)
  
  - when calling function no white space between function name and `(`
  ```python
  print(8)
  print(3 + 5)
  print(2*3 + 5)
  ```
  
  - 80 chars per line of code
  - don't use `()` unless needed, they have special meaning in python for tuples for example
    - **use** `if x < 3:` **not** `if(x < 3):`
  - use 4 spaces to indent
